ZH: 他经常忽视我在他面前的存在。
EN: He often ignores my presence in front of him.

ZH: 她忽视了我给她发的信息。
EN: She ignored the message I sent her.

ZH: 我忽视了他的警告，结果付出了代价。
EN: I disregarded his warning and suffered the consequences.

ZH: 他对这个问题的重要性完全忽视了。
EN: He completely overlooked the importance of this issue.

ZH: 请不要忽视我们的建议，这是对你有利的。
EN: Please do not disregard our advice, it is beneficial for you.

ZH: 孩子们常常忽视家长的规定。
EN: Children often disregard their parents' rules.

ZH: 我不想忽视你的感受，但有时我需要这样做。
EN: I don't want to ignore your feelings, but sometimes I need to.

ZH: 生态系统的保护是我们不能忽视的重要问题。
EN: The conservation of ecosystems is an important issue that we cannot overlook.

ZH: 他因为忽视细节而犯了很多错误。
EN: He made many mistakes because he neglected the details.

ZH: 你不能忽视他所做的努力。
EN: You can't disregard the effort he puts in.

ZH: 在这个项目中，别忽视我们的合作伙伴的意见。
EN: Don't overlook the opinions of our partners in this project.

ZH: 忽视这个问题会导致更大的麻烦。
EN: Ignoring this issue will lead to bigger troubles.

ZH: 不要忽视你的健康问题，及时就医是非常重要的。
EN: Do not neglect your health issues; seeking medical attention promptly is crucial.

ZH: 你不应该忽视他的建议，他是一个经验丰富的专家。
EN: You shouldn't dismiss his advice; he is an experienced expert.

ZH: 我原以为他会努力改变，但是他还是忽视了我的期望。
EN: I thought he would make an effort to change, but he still ignored my expectations.

ZH: 我希望大家不要忽视这个重要的问题。
EN: I hope everyone won't overlook this important issue.

ZH: 在这个人口普查中，我们不能忽视任何一个社区的数据。
EN: In this census, we can't ignore the data from any community.

ZH: 她不愿意面对现实，总是选择忽视问题。
EN: She doesn't want to face reality and always chooses to ignore the problems.

ZH: 只是因为你不喜欢某个人，并不意味着你可以忽视他的权利。
EN: Just because you don't like someone doesn't mean you can disregard their rights.

ZH: 忽视别人的感受是一种不尊重的行为。
EN: Ignoring someone's feelings is a disrespectful behavior.

ZH: 忽视这个警告可能会导致危险的后果。
EN: Ignoring this warning could lead to dangerous consequences.
